CSS Variables:
1. Apply --ion- prefix for Ionic framework variables
2. Apply --app- prefix for application-specific variables
3. Use kebab-case for all variable names
4. Cluster related variables together
5. Reference predefined font size variables:
    e.g., --app-font-size-sm, --app-font-size-lg
6. Reference predefined breakpoint variables

Variable Naming:
1. Select descriptive names reflecting purpose
2. Keep naming patterns consistent within groups
3. Use semantic color identifiers (e.g., navy-blue, soft-gray)
4. Define component-level color variables:         
   e.g., 
    --app-table-bg-color
    --app-table-header-bg-color
    --app-table-wrapper-bg-color
5. Create base variables then derive usage-specific ones for maintainability
   e.g.,
    --app-gray-light: #f2f2f2;
    --app-button-disabled-bg: var(--app-gray-light);
    --app-header-bg: var(--app-blue-light);

Variable Values:
1. Provide RGB values for colors when required
2. Reference other variables using var(--name) syntax
3. Specify font sizes in relative units (rem)
